snippet: The Emerson String Quartet stuck with Mostly Mozart’s bird theme, with Dvorak, and added trout to the mix, with Schubert.
abstract: Vivien Schweitzer reviews performance by the Emerson String Quartet and guest artists as part of the Mostly Mozart Festival at Alice Tully Hall.
lead_paragraph: The Emerson String Quartet stuck with Mostly Mozart’s bird theme, with Dvorak, and added trout to the mix, with Schubert.

headline.seo: Emerson String Quartet at Alice Tully Hall
headline.main: An Incessant Birdcall, Then Peaceful Fishing
